"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall distribution of water usage efficiency across districts and crops. Next, the user selects districts and crops of interest in View 1, filtering subsequent views. In View 2 at the [Exploration] level, the user examines average water efficiency grouped by irrigation methods and crop types. In parallel, the user explores correlations in View 3 between water efficiency and soil metrics. Through View 4, the user observes seasonal variations in water efficiency and irrigation practices by filtering seasons and districts. Detailed distributions of irrigation method efficiencies are revealed in View 5. Finally, View 6 provides a heatmap for identifying top-performing districts and crops in terms of water efficiency."